body_text.text:
The antisense RNA probe clearly showed positivity in the liver from 8 h p.i. The positive signal was blue and granular, and confined to the hepatocyte cytoplasm (Fig. 2
). Nuclei showed no reactivity. Sometimes, the signal was so intense as to mask the nucleus and cover the whole cellular surface. Labelled hepatocytes were scattered throughout the sections until 24 h p.i. (Fig. 3
). Their number constantly and significantly increased with time, reaching a maximum at 44 h p.i. (Fig. 4
). The liver and spleen samples of one rabbit, killed at 16 h p.i., was negative with both probes.
